div.p:
The supplied training and test sets from kaggle already appear relatively well-prepared and ready for analytic consumption. The main challenge to setting up an architecture to consume such a large dataset is how to process it on local compute. This project will follow a pseudo
medallion architecture
to transform the large dataset from raw (bronze) to a corrected version with more memory efficient data-types and exclusion of records with missing values (silver) to finally a set with engineered features, balanced classes and in general model consumption level data (gold). Additionally the polars package will be utilitized for its data streaming capabilities to process data in batches as it moves through this pipeline.
